Description: Herkimer County Community College is a school in Herkimer.
Full Description: The picturesque Adirondack Mountains in upstate New York are a perfect setting for students who want to obtain an associate’s degree, earn a certificate or plan to later transfer to a four-year college. Herkimer County Community College (HCCC) also offers affordable non-credit training programs as well as completely online certificate programs. HCCC is one of the largest residential community colleges, offering on-campus housing to qualified students. It is also host to an outstanding, championship athletic program. Herkimer offers over forty degree and certificate programs as well as more than twenty year-degree programs and one four-year certificate program through their Internet Academy online series. The academics at HCCC are structured for hands-on learning at state-of-the-art facilities. Applications for admission to degree or certificate programs for resident applicants should include proof of a high school diploma, GED, or four-year equivalent documentation for home schooled individuals. For non-residents, additional information is required, with minimum GPA/GED scores required. SAT/ACT test results should also be submitted. Tuition and fees vary for resident and non-resident students. Current tuition and fee listings can be found on the HCCC website. New York residents may be eligible for both federal and state financial aid programs. Prospective students should first fill out the FAFSA and receive their awards before applying for additional financial aid. Non-residents are encouraged to apply for state aid from their home states. Limited scholarships are available to qualified students who fill out a separate scholarship application. There is always something happening on campus at HCCC. Numerous student organizations, campus events and athletic events are a part of campus life. There are health services available, and for those interested in becoming a mentor as well as developing leadership and public speaking skills, HCCC offers a student ambassador program.

Description: The Finker-Frenkel Family Foundation funds world-changing initiatives both at home and abroad.
Full Description: As a child growing up in Russia, Dr. Lazar “Lonya” Finker remembers being raised in an atmosphere of generosity. Though theirs was a family of humble means, giving was nonetheless a way of life.  This simple yet profound example instilled in him a lifelong practice of heartfelt philanthropy. A practice shared by his wife, Dr. Raissa Frenkel, and imparted to their sons, Eugene and Steven. Through strong work ethics and deeply held values, Drs. Finker and Frenkel have achieved extraordinary success. Success that could indeed be due in large part to a law of reciprocity: “The generous soul will be made rich, and he who waters will also be watered himself.”* Modeling the example set by their parents and grandparents, they follow a personal policy of extending help to any who had needs, regardless of race, religion or color. “The Foundation is a legacy that will hold future generations together to change the world.” Such was Dr. Finker’s motivation to create the Finker-Frenkel Family Foundation. He realized that great progress is not brought about in a day, but rather is the product of the collaboration of generations building upon one another’s advancements. As such, it would require the commitment of generations dedicated to the continuation of the work. Who better to make that commitment than a family that could pass the torch from parent to child, from child to grandchild?
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Education, Health Care, Other, Social Impact
